metadata.name: Bloomside of The Past Field #83
metadata.description:
Made this work as a part of trying to make misprint effects, while maintaining the square form.
The scene are the flowers and other vegetations. Sometimes the scene will have the rain, snow and other weathers.

I imagined the scene was a form of painting, drawing or pictures on the postcard. So, all of them will have been signed as a loved sign, dusted sign (the spiders will come) and left unsigned. 

-----
The grain function which I used from Gorilla Sun Fx(text)
written in p5js. 
-----
my friends are married and getting married. I was left and I'm growing the flowers for myself in the sideline of the park, house, or elsewhere.

metadata.name: Layers #75
metadata.description:
It's the first time I really delved into studying about P5JS

I spent the last one collecting generative art and it made my passion for all this just grow, as a collector I wanted to move forward and want to do something more and so developed this project. 

I've been a designer for almost 10 years, an art director for over 1 year, I work all day with design every day, Photoshop and its infinite layers haunt me all day, as my passion wanted to insert something related there in my work so I thought of "layers" and thus "Layers" was born, layers and layers, specifically of rectangles one on top of the other forming the interactions of this work.

5 Styles:

Dunes:
Curves, some sharp and others less so, some remind me of sand dunes.

moiree:
It reminds me a little of compositions with a Moiré effect, forming curves where there is the presence of shadows giving relief.

Arranged:

A style where there is a certain organization of lines, but not perfect.

Strips:

Strips of colors on top of each other.

Harmonic:
It forms flat compositions, they are more organized layers.


17 Color Palettes based on famous works such as paintings and compositions:

"Mondrian - Composition with Large Red Plane, Yellow, Black, Gray and Blue / Piet Mondrian"
"Monalisa - Leonardo da Vinci"
"Portrait - Van Gogh self-portrait / Van Gogh"
"Venus - The Birth of Venus / Sandro Botticelli"
"Memory - The Persistence of Memory / Salvador Dalí"
"Son - The Son of Man /René Magritte"
"Guitarist - The Old Guitarist / Pablo Picasso"
"Canna - Red Canna / Georgia O'Keeffe"
"Drowning - Drowning Girl / Roy Lichtenstein"
"American - American Gothic / Grant Wood"
"Sunrise - Impression, Sunrise / Claude Monet"
"Creation - The Creation of Adam / Michelangelo"
"Girl - Girl with a Pearl Earring / Johannes Vermeer"
"Square - Black Square / Kazimir Malevich"
"Wave - The Great Wave off Kanagawa / Katsushika Hokusai"
"Wanderer - Wanderer above the Sea of ​​Fog / David Friedrich"
"Scream - The Scream / Edvard Munch"

"Layers" uses grains/noises function by Gorilla Sun, thanks for sharing your article with us! Article https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain

Created with p5js / Alex Benedith

metadata.name: Sketch F #44
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch F(ree). A gift to all Sketch A-E collectors. The underlying grid structure from A-E remains, but more variation on size and distribution is added. Many more color palettes are introduced. Grid size, padding, and colors vary.

metadata.name: Commune #22
metadata.description:
A minimalist composition with a nod towards architecture.

2932 bytes of Vanilla JS.

For more info, see article linked below: Me, Commune, Etc.

In live mode:
’S’ : save as svg (without grain)
‘P’ : save as png (3780x2673)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=w’ : wood grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 7560 × 5346 (Chrome only)

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save the png with those settings applied.

metadata.name: Ocean #110
metadata.description:
Ocean is my second long-form generative work continuing my exploration of creating visual designs with polygons. As found with the name, Ocean, this piece is inspired by patterns of ocean waves, storms, typhoons, and urchins. Ocean is composed of six layout variations and four color palettes with a few singular inspirations.

Click on the image to save 1400x1400 png

Created By: lukaszgraphz
Twitter: https://twitter.com/lukasz_x2

Art: November 2022
Created with p5js and the Pacific Ocean
CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: Penumbra #193
metadata.description:
Penumbra is a geometric exploration of the possible outcomes from 3 basic rules:

1) Place some walls
2) Place some light sources
3) Draw the resulting shadows

This series is a small thank you to the collectors of Umbra :)

metadata.name: Mooncakes: Happy Mid Autumn Festival 2022 #1543
metadata.description:
To celebrate the Moon Festival with Mooncakes, we have created a quest to introduce everyone to fxhash. As part of that quest on mooncakes.fun, users are encouraged to mint this generative token.

This is a layered image composition using the Mooncakes site images on a 1920x1080 canvas. The image elements are randomly assigned position, scale, tint, and blur according to a ruleset which generates a Mid Autumn Festival scene made up of: Moon, Clouds, Stars, Lanterns, and Lotuses.

Special filters, shapes and colors are included as rare features, as well as a couple of surprises.
